name: Eyecubes Red-Eyed Tree Frog
description:
An "eyecube" from Red-Eyed Tree Frog, an arboreal hylid native to Neotropical rainforests from Mexico, throughout Central America, to Colombia. Nocturnal carnivores, they hide in the rain forest canopy and ambush crickets, flies, and moths with their long, sticky tongues.

/ Eyecubes are the animals of the our virtual spaces. They roam the worlds. They behave differently from human avatars. 
/ Eyecubes are marrying the fading biodiversity of the real world with the potentials of the virtual worlds.
